// required apis
const logToConsole = require('logToConsole');
const injectScript = require('injectScript');
const queryPermission = require('queryPermission');
const inWindow = require('callInWindow');

const lhUid = data.lhUserId;
const lhIdId = data.lhIdentityId;
const key = data.apiKey;
const source = 'https://track.getlighthouse.io/track.js';
// If the user chose to log debug output, initialize the logging method
const log = data.debug ? logToConsole : (() => {});
// If the script loaded successfully, log a message and signal success
const onSuccess = () => {
  log('Lighthouse: Script loaded successfully.');
    inWindow('wwTrack', lhUid, lhIdId, key);
  data.gtmOnSuccess();
};
// If the script fails to load, log a message and signal failure
const onFailure = () => {
  log('Lighthouse: Script load failed.');
  data.gtmOnFailure();
};

if (queryPermission('inject_script', source)) {
  injectScript(source, onSuccess, onFailure);
} else {
  log('Lighthouse: Script load failed due to permissions mismatch.');
  data.gtmOnFailure();
}
